{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 I think self-organization as Willats uses it above is problematic because it could be misconstrued as the invisible hand of the market which ideologues proclaim needs to be left alone, forever, in order to \u8220"self-organize\u8221" supply and demand of goods and services. It\u8217's a good thing that there is a license that explicitly negates that. It\u8217's GPLv3. The specific transformation in the self that I\u8217'm aiming at changing is attitudes towards constructed narratives designed to create cult followings. They are not helping to deepen the audience\u8217's relationship with the artwork. Giving the audience access to the GPLv3 licensed code on The Public Internet might not do that all of the time but it is a thing to try instead of going along with a prescribed method mindlessly.\par}
