{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This quote keeps popping up all over the place. Later on in a video game called {\i Assassin\u8217's Creed}. Everyone is sampling it. The origin is more blurred by every use of it. It especially effects searchability on the commercial internet as the search engine (you know which one, the dominant one) is \u8220"optimizing\u8221" by finding and fanning flames into resonances. When a resonance becomes feedback it can be used as a new signal to replace the old one. True origins are being overwritten.\par}
